botanichorizons.BH_FLOWERS.body=Documentos antiguos hablan de flores mágicas, mas parecen haberse extinguido. Las setas que has visto en cuevas profundas parecen tener propiedades similares a esas flores. Con la invención de la alquimia piensas que podrías recrearlas a base de remoar las esporas de las setas en la esencia de las plantas de la superficie.
botanichorizons.BH_FLOWERDUPE.body=Estas flores han demostrado ser muy difíciles de hacer crecer silvestres, y no llevan bien lo de ser rotas. Afortunadamente, tus avances en taumaturgia han resultado en una nueva receta botánica. Ahora p uedes cortar una rama, mojarla en este mejunje, y desarrollará nuevas raíces.
botanichorizons.BH_FLOWERCOLOUR.body=Hasta ahora tus intentos alquímicos han resultado en flores de la misma especie. Este nuevo método te permite copiar el color de otra cosa y aplicarlo en la planta.
botanichorizons.BH_BLACKLOTUS.body=During your studies you noticed that the black mystic flower seems especially akin to absorbing mana. Almost as if it is somewhat incomplete? By providing enough mana and catalyst material it is possible to turn it into black lotus.<BR><BR>Some of the mana can be extracted back by dissolving it in a mana pool, but looks like most of it is simply... gone?<BR><BR>Even with enormous amounts of mana infused, the black lotus still continues to absorb more. You only have to wonder how dark it can get.
botanichorizons.BH_MUSHROOMS.body=A veces está bien retroceder. Has revisado tu método de creación de flores y has conseguido destransformarlas en setas.
botanichorizons.BH_ALTAR.body=Revelaciones recientes en artificería te han revelado como infudir varios objetos en otro. Y para darle más sabor has decidido hacerlo más "al natural."
botanichorizons.BH_TERRASTEEL.body=Publicaciones recientes hablan del poder del uranio. Has decidido meterle energía a un metal y has hallado algo nuevo. Parece aún más radiante al ojo novato, pero tú sabes que es simplemente más verde.
botanichorizons.BH_ALFHEIM.body_0=Hay rumores que hablan de una dimensión aún más lejana que el nether. Ahora que tienes mucha más energía con la que trabajar, es hora de construir un portal. Primero necesitamos un marco afinado a las energías involucradas.
botanichorizons.BH_ALFHEIM.body_1=La segunda parte es el mecanismo de control. Es muy difícil abrir un portal dimensional, y hace falta maś ajuestes para poner las fuentes de maná y los aparatos redirectores en el punto justo para crear un enlace estable.
botanichorizons.BH_ALCHEMY_CATALYST.body=Alchemy with ingredients is nice, but you think you can do even better. You have designed a machine that can replace some ingredients with mana.
botanichorizons.BH_CONJURATION_CATALYST.body=You've managed to improve your earlier catalyst to replace all material resources with mana. The downside is that it can only create copies of simple materials.
botanichorizons.BH_MANA_PYLON.body=Using bookshelves to fuel your enchantment processes sounds oldfashioned to you. Instead you've discovered a way of passively infusing your enchantments by focusing aura through a mana-rich device. It also seems to work as an infusion stabiliser.
botanichorizons.BH_NATURA_PYLON.body=You needed something more powerful. This device can focus enough aura to pierce holes in the dimensional fabric. Only very small holes though.
botanichorizons.BH_GAIA_PYLON.body=Your aura-focusing research has reached the pinnacle of thaumaturgic knowledge. Other thaumaturges call you mad over the energies involved and tell you to stop or even flee the scene, but they just don't seem to understand. After all, tearing a big hole in the fabric of this world is EXACTLY what you want to do.
botanichorizons.BH_BREWERY.body=Your latest research has resulted in a breakthrough in potion making. You improved the process so that you have bigger yields with less impurities. You can even store the result in one bottle and take an occasional swig without the outside air ruining the brew's properties.
botanichorizons.BH_ALFGLASS_FLASK.body=This extradimensional glass turns out to be an excellent container for potions. Since the glass is already highly magical, this flask absorbs less from the potion itself, leaving more for you.
botanichorizons.BH_TERRASTEEL_SWORD.body=Terrasteel is a much more potent material than Thaumium, so you decided to upgrade your existing sword of the Zephyr with some.
botanichorizons.BH_TERRASTEEL_PICK.body=Terrasteel as its name implies has a high affinity with terrestrial materials. Your old pickaxe of the core seems like a good starting template.
botanichorizons.BH_TERRASTEEL_AXE.body=Your latest magimetallurgic invention has good affinity with natural substances. With some extra work you've now created a process to apply terrasteel to the Axe of the Stream.
botanichorizons.BH_MANASTEEL_WRENCH.body=You tried making a simple wrench out of basic Manasteel. It works, but wasn't very durable.<BR><BR>You tried putting a bit more magic in it, and you noticed two things: The wrench repaired itself, and more curiously, it now has an innate aversion to anything mechanical.<BR><BR>This wrench works well at dismantling blocks, but is not very good at other manipulations, or handling non-mechanical items. The soft material isn't very good at dislodging high-quality nuts from their bolts either.<BR><BR>You're sure further research could help.
botanichorizons.BH_MANASTEEL_WRENCH_XL.body=¡Próximamente!
botanichorizons.BH_TERRASTEEL_WRENCH.body=Your invention of Terrasteel is a promising substitute for your earlier wrench. Sure enough, the result is a much more durable tool, and the sturdy material is also able to disassemble more things than its predecessor.<BR><BR>What didn't improve is its aversion to mechanical structures. Actually, you feel that this feature is even stronger now, though it has nowhere to go. This internal conflict seems to hinder the natural qualities of Terrasteel, and you wonder how you can improve on it.
botanichorizons.BH_TERRASTEEL_WRENCH_XL.body=It took a small revelation that trying to make such a wrench repair things was never going to work, and instead it could be much more interesting to amplify its destructive powers. By letting nature's aversion to mechanical structures run amok, this wrench now wants to fly out of your hand to break the remotest parts of a structure and fetches you some of the remains.<BR><BR>By targeting the heart of a machine, this wrench will systematically remove all of its mechanical parts. It is also VERY hungry for mana.
botanichorizons.BH_ELVEN_WRENCH.body=After you recently got your hands on some Elementium by trading with the Elves, you take the opportunity to turn your most recent batch into a wrench.<BR><BR>Much as you expected, this material is both slightly more resilient and more capable than Manasteel. You still didn't manage to make the wrench able to break natural constructs, nor will it repair or tweak mechanical ones. It still feels like a nice improvement over the original.<BR><BR>For all the mana you poured into it, it somehow feels... behaved. Curious.
botanichorizons.BH_ELVEN_WRENCH_XL.body=Now that you've seen Elven Elementium in action, you notice how it has an innate ability to recognise what it has touched. You have seen how an armor made of the material tries to defend its wearer. This thought seems to open up a new area of wrench-making.<BR><BR>You devise a new enchantment that makes the material believe individual blocks are an adversary. By tapping them once, you can now teach your wrench to target only selected blocks.<BR><BR>As a final tweak, you decide to add some dragonstones to store extra mana, and make it do more work at a time.
botanichorizons.BH_LAPUTA.body_0=Sometimes you have to show off. You found a way to infuse a patch of land and make it float in the sky. It seems to be pretty difficult though. The shard of laputa works as a temporary vessel to house the energies required, before it's pushed into the ground.
botanichorizons.BH_LAPUTA.body_1=Since the amount of energy needed increases per area of land you want to float, you have quickly realised that you need better and better materials to do the job. The return on investment also doesn't appear to be that good.
botanichorizons.BH_VIRUS.body=You've ventured into an odd corner of carnivorous plants and created something nastier. At least animal test subjects seem not to be a moral issue for you.

